1f:T629,Managed a portfolio of 5 to 9 diverse job openings at a time. Recruitment was conducted across various business sectors, including:
	1.	Manufacturing personnel (e.g., design engineers, mechanical engineers, lean production specialists, project managers, workshop supervisors, lathe operators, equipment maintenance and repair mechanics, testing lab engineers, and general workers).
	2.	Construction (e.g., surveyors, site supervisors, foremen, project documentation engineers, crane mechanics, roofers).
	3.	Logistics (e.g., logistics managers, dispatchers).
	4.	Wholesale and retail trade (e.g., sales consultants, sales managers).

Geographical scope: Primarily the Ural Federal District, with additional experience recruiting in Kazan and Moscow.

Key responsibilities included:
	•	Conducting on-site meetings with clients to clarify company details, internal processes, job requirements, recruitment procedures, and preferred communication methods.
	•	Performing labor market analysis to identify industry trends, candidate expectations, and employer offerings. This included presenting sample resumes to align on the target candidate profile.
	•	Handling the entire recruitment process, including candidate sourcing, conducting interviews, and organizing meetings either on the client’s premises or within the recruitment agency for confidential searches.
	•	Preparing client documentation (e.g., candidate resumes with detailed assessments, invoices, and completion reports).

The E-Staff system was utilized for maintaining and managing the candidate database.18: [
